A Monday to remember! Relive the magic of the 2021 Met Gala.  #metgala #MetInAmerica

Directed by @bardiazeinali
Director of Photography @packdrawn
Steadicam @yoshisteadiop

More than the launch of unparalleled works of jewelry craft, @Bulgari's Magnifica High Jewelry collection is a celebration of rebirth. Honored through magnificent muses, music, and Milan, take a look at Bvlgari's latest high jewelry collection.
 
Models: @vittoria, @lilyaldridge @heconghc, @solangesmith and @blesnyaminher
Special Guests: @andreabocelliofficial @beatricevenezi
Project by @oma.eu
Director @tommaso.ottomano
DOP@ mrcodepa
Stylist @sagliogeraldine
Music @guazzonemarco 
Production @studio.april
#Bvlgari #BvlgariJewelry #BvlgariHighJewelry #BvlgariMagnifica #Milan

node.text: After making her #NYFW modeling debut at @ProenzaSchouler, @EllaEmhoff landed a knitwear collaboration with Batsheva Hay (@batshevadress). The 21-year-old student, model, and designer met up with Hay amid NYFW—and #GoodMorningVogue was there to capture their conversations about materials, fit, and texture, plus Ella's rise to fame in the wake of the inauguration of President Joe Biden and Emhoff’s step-mother, Kamala Harris, in January.

node.text: This month, Vogue joined forces with an army of photographers and models all around the globe—stable Zoom connections required, please!—and sent the best and brightest of the new collections via courier services everywhere from Beijing to Brazil, Lagos to Los Angeles. Our concept? Simple, glorious movement: After a year of stasis, immobility and lockdowns, we wanted to see spring fashion breaking free. These are the looks we love, shot by the photographers we adore, on the run and out for a walk, a swim, a dance. Tap the link in our bio to see more.

node.text:
Today, @KamalaHarris became the first woman of color ever sworn in as vice president of the United States.

To celebrate this moment, twelve young women discussing what it means to them to see a Black woman of Indian descent elected to the second-highest office in the land. “Every little girl sees that this is a country of possibility,” @KamalaHarris states in one address, and that sentiment is widely echoed. “She reminds me every day that I am capable and worthy of my wildest dreams,” says one participant.

Director @rombokob
Producer @aliwebb_producer
Casting Director: Rebecca Dealy
Archival Research: Manon Blackman
Editor @ann_lupo
GFX @horatiobaltz
Color @carlosfloresfilms
Mix @cstropko
Post Production @forager.tv

node.title: 12 Girls on What Kamala Harris Becoming Vice President Means to Them

node.text: Throughout the political tumult of 2020, @janayathefuture was one of the most prominent voices to become a source of healing and hope. Reflecting on this week’s events, Khan points out the lack of police presence at the Capitol, a fact that exposes, in their own words, “a clear double standard for how Black protestors have been treated over the past several years. What we know to be true is that there is a way that white rage is celebrated in this country and Black grief is criminalized.” To hear more, make sure to check out Khan’s Sunday Sermons, returning tomorrow 1/10  at 12PM PST on their account.

node.title: @janayathefuture on Moving Forward from the Capitol Riots

node.text:
What's a day in @chikalogy's life like? From singing with her pup to jamming in the studio, watch what happened when we spent 24 hours with the star.
Directed by @dreambigdobigger
Produced by Moonshot Management

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue on September 20, 2021 tagging @christopherjohnrogers, @zerinaakers, and @kaylareefer. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
Michaela Coel made history at the 2021 #Emmys. As the first Black woman to win Outstanding Writing in a Limited Series, Coel received a well-deserved accolade for her powerful and personal drama, I May Destroy You. To honor the evening’s spirit and the continued success of her groundbreaking series, Coel chose a red carpet look that was bright, bold, and uplifting. Her @christopherjohnrogers-designed skirt felt like a breath of fresh air, and from the moment the designer presented his sketch, Coel’s stylist @zerinaakers knew it was something special.

Tap the link in our bio for all the details, and to see more from Coel's journey to the red carpet. Photo: @KaylaReefer

node.text: #LFW is back in full swing, albeit with a smaller schedule and a mix of physical and digital shows. The city feels more alive than it has in months, and @styledumonde’s Acielle is on the ground to shoot the best looks outside the shows and presentations. Tap the link in our bio to see more of this season's top street style looks.

One of the most popular trends from our fall 2021 trend report was dubbed collage therapy. Whether quilted, patched, or paneled, the trend feels just right for the mood of the fall season, and this season's top styles—including dresses, midi skirts, and jackets—do not disappoint.

Tap the link in our bio to shop our top patchwork picks for fall. Photographed by Paul Wetherell, Vogue, October 2018.

The 2021 #EmmyAwards full winners list is in! Among those who took home a gold statuette was Olivia Colman winning the Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series award for her performance in the series, "The Crown."

Tap the link in bio to see the extensive list of tonight's winners at the 73rd Emmy Awards.
 
Photographed by @annieleibovitz, styled by @tonnegood, Vogue, October 2019.

node.text:
The 2021 #EmmyAwards red carpet was on fire tonight. The awards ceremony has a history of delivering tons of glamorous looks, and the stars did not disappoint by busting out the finest eveningwear the runways have to offer. The stunning and effortlessly glamorous @cynthiaerivo wore a fitted @louisvuitton gown with bright feather detail that floated down the red carpet with style and grace.

Tap the link in bio to see more red carpet moments from the 73rd annual Emmy Awards. 
Photo: @jahmadbalugo

node.text: @erdem's 15th anniversary collection – and first runway show since the pandemic, was presented in the colonnade of the British Museum (in Bloomsbury) at #LFW today. Tap the link in bio to see the full spring summer 2022 collection, inspired by the wardrobes of Bloomsbury’s best: Edith Sitwell and Ottoline Morrell. Photographed by @styledumonde

node.text:
We’ve seen sustainability become a growing trend on the red carpet in recent years — and this year’s #MetGala was no different. Considering the theme was In America: A Lexicon Of Fashion, it’s fitting that it was US designers who were leading the way on this front, with @bodepersonal making a rare venture into evening wear by creating a custom @bode embroidered two-piece for @lorde that celebrated the Arts and Crafts movement, featuring antique embellishments dating from 1890 onwards.

To see more of the best sustainable looks from the Met Gala 2021, tap the link in bio.

node.text:
Walking into the 2021 #MetGala guests were greeted by a grand oak tree made of recycled materials, surrounded by a wild field of wheatgrass made by floral designer @raulavilainc in collaboration with landscape designer @miranda.brooks.gardens. 
The oak tree is our country’s national tree, and is nearly as diverse as the United States’ population: there are 60 different oak species growing from coast to coast. “The 2021 Great Hall centerpiece is the metaphorical manifestation of the strength and endurance rooted in the American people,” explains Àvila.

Tap the link in bio to learn more about this year's grand oak centerpiece and the details that went into making it spectacular.
